    "title": "תהלים מ״ז | (Psalms 47) Dieser Psalm wird siebenmal vor dem Schofer blasen wiederholt (translation by Yehoshua Heshil Miro, 1829)",
    "author": "Andreas Rusterholz (transcription)",
    "coauthors": [
        {
            "name": "Andreas Rusterholz (transcription)",
            "bio": "Andreas Rusterholz is a professor of Theology (New Testament and Hermeneutics) at Kwansei Gakuin University School of Humanities Department of Literature and Linguistics. He translated (together with Takako Noguchi, 1943-2017) <em>Jüdische Religion</em> by Günter Stemberger (Beck 1995) into Japanese: <em>Yudayakyo - Rekishi, Shinko, Bunka</em> [Judaism: History, Faith, Culture], Kyobunkwan 2015.",
            "website": "http://researchers.kwansei.ac.jp/view?l=en&amp;u=21462",
            "avatar": "https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/andreas-rusterholz-96x96.jpg",
            "profile_link": "https://opensiddur.org/profile/andreas-rusterholz"
        },
        {
            "name": "Yehoshua Heshil Miro",
            "bio": "Yehoshua Heshil ben Rabbi Binyamin Miro (fl. first-half 19th c.) was a writer and Jewish educator in Prussia, an early advocate and teacher of Jewish girls. He worked as a professor at a private school, and a teacher at the <a href=\"https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Königliche_Wilhelms-Schule\">Königliche Wilhelms-Schule</a> (and possibly also the <a href=\"https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Industrieschule_für_israelitische_Mädchen\">Industrial School for Israelite Girls</a>), in then Prussian Breslau. We know very little else about Miro aside from his publication of a popular anthology of teḥinot for German speaking women first published in 1829. If you know more about Miro, please <a href=\"/contact/\">contact us</a>.",
            "website": "",
            "avatar": "https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Keith-Evans-Green-Tree-Yellow-Field-CC-BY-SA-250x250.jpg",
            "profile_link": "https://opensiddur.org/profile/yehoshua-heshil-miro"
        },
        {
            "name": "Bnei Qoraḥ",
            "bio": "The Bnei Qoraḥ (sons of Ḳoraḥ a/k/a Qoraḥites) were an important branch of the singers of the Kohathite division (2 Chronicles 20:19). Eleven psalms are attributed to the Qoraḥites: Psalms 42, Psalms 44 - 49, Psalms 84, Psalms 85, Psalms 87, and Psalms 88. Some of the sons of Qoraḥ also were \"porters\" of the temple (1 Chronicles 9:17-19); one of them was over \"things that were made in the pans\" (v31), i.e., the baking in pans for the meat-offering (Leviticus 2:5). (via <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Korahites\">wikipedia</a>)",
            "website": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Korahites",
            "avatar": "https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Keith-Evans-Green-Tree-Yellow-Field-CC-BY-SA-250x250.jpg",
            "profile_link": "https://opensiddur.org/profile/bnei-korah"
        },
        {
            "name": "Aharon N. Varady (translation)",
            "bio": "Aharon Varady (M.A.J.Ed./JTSA Davidson) is a volunteer translator for the Open Siddur Project. If you find any mistakes in his translations, please <a href=\"/contact/\">let him know</a>. <em>Shgiyot mi yavin; Ministarot Naqeni</em> <span lang=\"he\" class=\"scribe\">שְׁגִיאוֹת מִי־יָבִין; מִנִּסְתָּרוֹת נַקֵּנִי</span> \"Who can know all one's flaws? From hidden errors, correct me\" (Psalms 19:13). If you'd like to directly support his work, please consider donating via his <a href=\"https://www.patreon.com/aharonium\">Patreon account</a>. (Varady also <a href=\"/profile/aharon-varady-transcription/\">transcribes prayers</a> and <a href=\"/profile/aharon-varady/\">contributes his own original work</a> besides serving as the primary <em>shammes</em> for the Open Siddur Project and its website, opensiddur.org.)",
            "website": "https://aharon.varady.net",
            "avatar": "https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/Aharon-Varady-2002.jpg",
            "profile_link": "https://opensiddur.org/profile/aharon-varady-translation"
        }
